        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 3:49PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 349 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Milan, or 13 miles west of Grants, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grants, Milan and San Rafael in Cibola County.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 80 and 81.

This includes the following recreation areas...
Ojo Redondo Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
